# AI Engine

## Approach

- Hybrid: rule base + ML + safety bounds.
- Never send unvalidated data into the model — validation layer first.

## Required prediction output

Every prediction must include:

- `irrigation_needed` (bool)
- `duration` (minutes, optional if not needed)
- `risk_level` (`low | medium | high | critical`)
- `confidence_score` (0–100)
- `explanation` (Turkish, human-readable)

## Safety

- Confidence < 60 → do not recommend automation.
- Missing critical fields → mark analysis as limited and lower confidence.
- Example thresholds: moisture < 30% + rain < 20% + last irrigation > 24h → irrigate; moisture > 70% → over-irrigation risk.

## Datasets

- Use fixed scenarios under `ai/datasets/` — do not generate random demo data.
